==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Similiter
<hw>Si*mil"i*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., in like
manner.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The technical name of the form by
which either party, in pleading, accepts the issue tendered by his
opponent; -- called sometimes a <altname>joinder in
issue</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Similitude</ent>⟦br⟧
